00:04:05,640 --> 00:04:09,792
There's a story going around
about a cursed video.

44
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:11,638
What kind of video it is?

45
00:04:12,600 --> 00:04:14,477
The version I've heard is,

46
00:04:14,680 --> 00:04:17,399
a scary woman appears,

47
00:04:17,600 --> 00:04:20,239
saying, "You'll die in one week."

48
00:04:20,440 --> 00:04:21,634
That's what I've heard.

49
00:04:22,280 --> 00:04:24,271
It interrupts late-night TV.

50
00:04:24,480 --> 00:04:26,994
Then there's a telephone call.

51
00:04:27,680 --> 00:04:30,114
The late-night programme
on which channel?

52
00:04:30,320 --> 00:04:31,992
What I've heard is

53
00:04:32,200 --> 00:04:34,111
some local channel in Izu.

54
00:04:34,320 --> 00:04:35,878
- In Izu?
- Yes.

55
00:04:36,080 --> 00:04:40,039
Is it really a good idea
to use this stuff?

56
00:04:41,240 --> 00:04:42,593
Why not?

57
00:04:53,600 --> 00:04:56,876
You'll die unless you make a copy
and show it to others...

58
00:04:57,080 --> 00:04:58,195
Yes.

59
00:04:58,400 --> 00:05:01,119
I have to confirm that story
with someone.

60
00:05:03,040 --> 00:05:04,996
Have you heard from Ms Asakawa?

61
00:05:05,200 --> 00:05:06,315
No.

62
00:05:07,320 --> 00:05:09,550
The police called about her, too.

63
00:05:09,760 --> 00:05:10,829
Yeah?

64
00:05:13,160 --> 00:05:14,388
Excuse me...

65
00:05:15,200 --> 00:05:18,237
Can I see Ms Reiko Asakawa?

66
00:05:19,440 --> 00:05:20,793
Well...

67
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:22,399
She's not in at the moment.

68
00:05:25,560 --> 00:05:27,278
There's a story going around

69
00:05:27,480 --> 00:05:29,789
about a cursed video.

70
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:31,479
What kind of video it is?

71
00:05:31,680 --> 00:05:33,318
The version I've heard is,

72
00:05:33,520 --> 00:05:36,273
a scary woman appears,

73
00:05:36,480 --> 00:05:39,074
saying 'You'll die in one week. "

74
00:05:39,280 --> 00:05:40,759
That's what I've heard.

75
00:05:40,960 --> 00:05:42,359
It interrupts late-night TV.

76
00:05:42,560 --> 00:05:43,788
Wait!

77
00:05:52,760 --> 00:05:54,796
Do you know anything about Asakawa?

78
00:05:56,320 --> 00:05:58,231
We haven't been able to contact her.

79
00:06:01,480 --> 00:06:04,040
A man named Ryuji T akayama is dead.

80
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:06,274
T akayama?

81
00:06:06,880 --> 00:06:09,519
Ms Asakawa's ex.

82
00:06:26,680 --> 00:06:29,035
The police came once.

83
00:06:29,240 --> 00:06:31,356
She's been away for a while.

84
00:06:31,560 --> 00:06:33,471
Did they go inside?

85
00:06:34,280 --> 00:06:36,635
No, not at the time.

86
00:06:39,560 --> 00:06:41,039
Go ahead.

87
00:07:48,040 --> 00:07:49,473
Ms Takano.

88
00:08:01,160 --> 00:08:02,513
What is this?

89
00:08:08,760 --> 00:08:10,512
A video tape?

90
00:08:27,360 --> 00:08:28,634
Dad,

91
00:08:28,840 --> 00:08:30,239
forgive me.

92
00:08:30,440 --> 00:08:32,590
This is to save Yoichi...

93
00:08:36,080 --> 00:08:37,308
Are you OK?

94
00:08:41,920 --> 00:08:43,148
Last time I saw her,

95
00:08:43,360 --> 00:08:46,318
Ms Asakawa asked me about the video.

96
00:08:47,760 --> 00:08:49,432
It was a human interest story.

97
00:08:49,640 --> 00:08:52,108
They don't give a single mother
important reports.

98
00:08:54,920 --> 00:08:56,876
Oh, yes, her boy.

99
00:08:58,040 --> 00:08:59,473
I'll go ask the school.

100
00:09:29,760 --> 00:09:31,159
Ms Asakawa?

101
00:09:31,360 --> 00:09:33,112
She's not in.

102
00:09:33,320 --> 00:09:35,072
This is the police.

103
00:09:35,280 --> 00:09:38,875
Reiko Asakawa's father was
found dead this morning.

104
00:09:51,120 --> 00:09:53,236
- Mr Kadokura?
- This way.

105
00:09:56,480 --> 00:09:58,550
- Sir.
- Yes?

106
00:09:58,800 --> 00:10:01,553
- I'm Omuta, from Shizuoka police.
- Thanks for coming.

107
00:10:01,760 --> 00:10:04,399
Any luck finding the daughter?

108
00:10:04,600 --> 00:10:06,158
None at all.

109
00:10:06,360 --> 00:10:08,828
How about the body found in the well?

110
00:10:09,040 --> 00:10:11,156
- We're rebuilding her face.
- Rebuild...

111
00:10:11,360 --> 00:10:13,032
As soon as we have her model,

112
00:10:13,240 --> 00:10:15,754
we'll take it
and ask around the area.

113
00:10:20,560 --> 00:10:22,869
He found the body first.

114
00:10:30,560 --> 00:10:32,471
Do you want to see it?

115
00:10:38,800 --> 00:10:41,360
People don't normally die like this.

116
00:11:11,080 --> 00:11:12,752
Was he making a copy?

117
00:11:13,880 --> 00:11:15,108
Well...

118
00:11:16,320 --> 00:11:19,278
We wonder if it has anything to do
with this note.

119
00:11:23,360 --> 00:11:25,271
DEAR RElKO,
I GOT RlD OF THE VlDEO.

120
00:11:25,480 --> 00:11:27,277
THERE lS NOTHlNG
TO WORRY ABOUT.

121
00:11:55,520 --> 00:11:56,509
No good.

122
00:11:56,720 --> 00:11:59,280
He's been absent
for more than 10 days.

123
00:11:59,480 --> 00:12:01,152
What's wrong?

124
00:12:01,360 --> 00:12:02,634
Nothing.

125
00:12:03,800 --> 00:12:06,917
Why are you looking for Ms Asakawa?

126
00:12:07,120 --> 00:12:10,954
I want to know what happened
to Dr Takayama.

127
00:12:13,720 --> 00:12:15,711
I'll check a bit more.

128
00:12:15,920 --> 00:12:17,831
If I find anything, I'll call you.

129
00:12:19,840 --> 00:12:21,319
See you.

130
00:13:21,320 --> 00:13:22,275
Yes?

131
00:13:22,480 --> 00:13:25,313
Police. Sorry for calling so late.

132
00:13:25,520 --> 00:13:27,636
I'd like to ask
about Mr Ryuji Takayama.

133
00:13:33,600 --> 00:13:36,160
Are you Mai T akano,
who found his body?

134
00:13:36,840 --> 00:13:37,955
Yes.

135
00:13:38,160 --> 00:13:39,752
May l...

136
00:13:41,080 --> 00:13:42,877
Please.

137
00:13:54,040 --> 00:13:56,429
Oh, I remember Mr T akayama.

138
00:13:56,640 --> 00:13:58,631
He taught maths.

139
00:13:58,840 --> 00:14:00,319
Are you...

140
00:14:00,520 --> 00:14:02,351
I'm his assistant.

141
00:14:02,560 --> 00:14:03,754
I see.

142
00:14:06,240 --> 00:14:07,070
Ms Takano,

143
00:14:07,880 --> 00:14:11,429
have you ever heard of
Sadako Yamamura?

144
00:14:13,040 --> 00:14:13,995
No.

145
00:14:14,200 --> 00:14:17,192
Shizuko Yamamura? Sadako's mother?

146
00:14:18,080 --> 00:14:18,910
No.

147
00:14:19,120 --> 00:14:21,236
Heihachiro lkuma?

148
00:14:21,440 --> 00:14:22,759
No.

149
00:14:25,800 --> 00:14:28,997
Ryuji Takayama and Reiko Asakawa
were investigating something.

150
00:14:29,200 --> 00:14:30,553
Is that right?

151
00:14:35,320 --> 00:14:37,709
I don't know.

152
00:14:37,920 --> 00:14:40,150
I see.

153
00:14:42,200 --> 00:14:43,428
Today,

154
00:14:43,640 --> 00:14:46,871
Reiko Asakawa's father
was found dead.

155
00:14:49,040 --> 00:14:51,315
He died the same way
as Mr Takayama.

156
00:14:51,520 --> 00:14:53,909
You know what I mean?

157
00:14:55,520 --> 00:14:57,670
Please go.

158
00:14:57,880 --> 00:14:59,996
They found the body in the well.

159
00:15:00,200 --> 00:15:04,352
An unidentified woman, who died
one or two years ago.

160
00:15:04,560 --> 00:15:06,915
But the well has been sealed
with concrete

161
00:15:07,120 --> 00:15:09,111
for 30 years.

162
00:15:09,320 --> 00:15:11,276
Can you believe it?

163
00:15:11,480 --> 00:15:14,313
In the dark well, for 30 years.

164
00:15:14,880 --> 00:15:17,633
Neither of her hands had nails.

165
00:15:17,840 --> 00:15:20,149
They were all found in
the sides of the well.

166
00:15:20,360 --> 00:15:22,635
Probably, she tried to climb out
so many times...

167
00:15:22,840 --> 00:15:24,398
Please go!

168
00:15:27,320 --> 00:15:28,958
Alright.

169
00:15:30,440 --> 00:15:33,079
If you find out anything about
Reiko Asakawa,

170
00:15:33,720 --> 00:15:35,472
call me at this number.

171
00:15:43,200 --> 00:15:44,519
I'm sorry,

172
00:15:44,720 --> 00:15:47,280
but this is such a strange case.

173
00:15:49,560 --> 00:15:51,198
What's it all about, the video?

174
00:15:55,400 --> 00:15:56,355
I don't know.

175
00:16:12,120 --> 00:16:13,758
No...

176
00:17:05,120 --> 00:17:06,758
Do you live around here?

177
00:17:06,960 --> 00:17:10,669
I can concentrate better here
than in my room.

178
00:17:10,880 --> 00:17:12,472
I see.

179
00:17:40,360 --> 00:17:41,509
OK, it's rolling.

180
00:17:41,720 --> 00:17:44,518
Let's continue.
Three seconds...

181
00:17:47,080 --> 00:17:48,991
So, you have to copy it

182
00:17:49,200 --> 00:17:51,714
and show it to someone else
within a week.

183
00:17:51,920 --> 00:17:54,878
Otherwise, a week later,
at the same time...

184
00:17:55,080 --> 00:17:58,231
So there's an original video
to make a copy from?

185
00:17:58,760 --> 00:17:59,510
Yes.

186
00:17:59,720 --> 00:18:02,473
Where does it come from?

187
00:18:02,680 --> 00:18:05,911
I've heard that it's just there
in the room.

188
00:18:06,120 --> 00:18:09,396
Everybody has some videos
they can't remember recording.

189
00:18:09,600 --> 00:18:12,034
Among those tapes,
they find a strange one.

190
00:18:12,240 --> 00:18:15,312
- How would you know that's the one?
- It's obvious if you see it.

191
00:18:15,520 --> 00:18:17,909
- Has anyone seen it?
- I know someone who has it.

192
00:18:20,600 --> 00:18:23,160
They're scared,
so show it to each other.

193
00:18:23,360 --> 00:18:25,078
It's going around among friends.

194
00:18:25,960 --> 00:18:27,871
Have you seen it?

195
00:18:32,640 --> 00:18:35,632
Is it possible to get me a copy?

196
00:18:39,680 --> 00:18:40,795
OK.

197
00:18:52,160 --> 00:18:53,275
Excuse me.

198
00:18:54,240 --> 00:18:55,514
Work out a price.

199
00:19:00,160 --> 00:19:03,311
Probably, Ms Asakawa was
after these four.

200
00:19:07,600 --> 00:19:09,511
A week after this date,

201
00:19:09,720 --> 00:19:12,029
all of them died at the same time.

202
00:19:16,280 --> 00:19:17,679
Hard to believe, isn't it?

203
00:19:18,600 --> 00:19:19,999
This girl, Tomoko,

204
00:19:20,200 --> 00:19:21,758
she was Ms Asakawa's niece.

205
00:19:22,600 --> 00:19:24,318
A girl was with her
when she died.

206
00:19:25,480 --> 00:19:26,708
Kurahashi...

207
00:19:27,680 --> 00:19:29,432
Masami Kurahashi.

208
00:19:29,640 --> 00:19:31,710
What happened to her?

209
00:19:32,800 --> 00:19:34,074
She's in the hospital.

210
00:19:34,280 --> 00:19:35,759
She can't speak.

211
00:19:36,560 --> 00:19:38,790
The hospital belongs
to your university.

212
00:19:48,320 --> 00:19:51,278
The doctor can't tell you anything
about patients' privacy.

213
00:19:51,480 --> 00:19:54,438
The questions should be
on the area of his research.

214
00:19:54,640 --> 00:19:55,914
Fine.

215
00:20:50,960 --> 00:20:52,552
This way, please.

216
00:21:16,120 --> 00:21:17,633
Ms Kurahashi!

217
00:21:23,760 --> 00:21:25,512
How are you feeling?

218
00:21:28,800 --> 00:21:32,349
Would you like to come out
to the balcony for a change?

219
00:21:33,280 --> 00:21:35,191
Doctor wants you to
get some fresh air.

220
00:21:49,480 --> 00:21:51,550
Are you still afraid of TV?

221
00:21:53,240 --> 00:21:54,559
It's fine.

222
00:21:54,760 --> 00:21:57,149
I'll bring a screen
so that you won't see it.

223
00:21:58,560 --> 00:21:59,675
OK?

224
00:22:02,120 --> 00:22:02,870
Doctor,

225
00:22:03,120 --> 00:22:04,792
they're here.

226
00:22:08,400 --> 00:22:09,389
Hello.

227
00:22:09,600 --> 00:22:10,919
I'm Kawajiri.

228
00:22:11,120 --> 00:22:12,155
Please.

229
00:22:18,760 --> 00:22:20,034
Our medical files are

230
00:22:20,280 --> 00:22:22,635
different from others,
because we attach photos.

231
00:22:28,040 --> 00:22:29,632
Do you know why?

232
00:22:29,840 --> 00:22:31,910
In case they run away?

233
00:22:32,120 --> 00:22:34,554
That's right.

234
00:22:35,200 --> 00:22:39,557
Illness can change the patient, even
their family can't recognise them.

235
00:22:39,760 --> 00:22:42,354
So we always take photos
when they arrive.

236
00:22:42,560 --> 00:22:45,711
But when we took photos
of this patient...

237
00:22:46,680 --> 00:22:49,114
..with our usual camera here...

238
00:22:50,360 --> 00:22:52,920
..a strange image came up.

239
00:23:28,200 --> 00:23:30,111
It's called 'spirit photography'.

240
00:23:31,040 --> 00:23:34,510
Something in a person's mind affects
the light and exposure.

241
00:23:34,720 --> 00:23:36,756
There were similar cases in the past.

242
00:23:36,960 --> 00:23:39,076
You mean, this photo was...

243
00:23:40,000 --> 00:23:42,468
We also tried just
having her hold a film.

244
00:23:53,880 --> 00:23:55,438
This shows a character clearly.

245
00:23:55,680 --> 00:23:58,752
SADA

246
00:24:04,440 --> 00:24:06,954
You may think I'm a strange doctor.

247
00:24:07,160 --> 00:24:10,072
All of my colleagues do.

248
00:24:11,640 --> 00:24:13,631
Do you know Ryuji Takayama?

249
00:24:14,240 --> 00:24:15,434
That's odd.

250
00:24:15,640 --> 00:24:17,756
He's the only one
who listened to me.

251
00:24:17,960 --> 00:24:21,430
He was once in medical school,
before he went in for maths.

252
00:24:22,160 --> 00:24:23,718
You know he died?

253
00:24:25,440 --> 00:24:27,317
What a shame.

254
00:24:28,400 --> 00:24:30,550
You didn't even come to his funeral.

255
00:25:07,320 --> 00:25:10,471
OK? This way,
you don't have to see it.

256
00:25:16,360 --> 00:25:18,191
No need to rush.

257
00:25:18,920 --> 00:25:20,592
Nice and slow.

258
00:25:21,240 --> 00:25:23,595
Take your time...

259
00:25:42,960 --> 00:25:44,234
What's wrong?

260
00:25:54,080 --> 00:25:56,389
Are you feeling bad?

261
00:26:02,960 --> 00:26:04,757
Ms Kurahashi...

262
00:27:37,280 --> 00:27:38,918
Take her to the treatment room.

263
00:28:07,800 --> 00:28:09,518
Tomoko...

264
00:28:14,960 --> 00:28:16,029
Tomoko...

265
00:28:31,760 --> 00:28:33,352
Help...

266
00:28:35,000 --> 00:28:36,831
Help me...

267
00:28:40,880 --> 00:28:42,393
Help her to get up!

268
00:28:43,680 --> 00:28:44,749
Are you OK?

269
00:28:54,200 --> 00:28:55,235
Help me!

270
00:29:23,200 --> 00:29:26,556
They said it was the first time
she's spoken.

271
00:29:30,200 --> 00:29:34,398
Are you going to continue
Ms Asakawa's report?

272
00:29:34,600 --> 00:29:36,238
Yes.

273
00:29:36,440 --> 00:29:38,158
You'd better stop.

274
00:29:39,120 --> 00:29:40,314
Why?

275
00:29:41,960 --> 00:29:43,552
Just stop it.

276
00:29:45,080 --> 00:29:47,036
