That's good.

563
01:12:46,040 --> 01:12:47,234
Can I have a word?

564
01:12:55,200 --> 01:12:56,519
He is controlled by

565
01:12:56,760 --> 01:12:58,193
anger.

566
01:12:58,400 --> 01:13:00,675
His anger summons Sadako.

567
01:13:01,200 --> 01:13:02,872
He can't control it.

568
01:13:04,600 --> 01:13:06,556
My equipment should arrive today.

569
01:13:06,760 --> 01:13:09,149
I'll try to eliminate
Sadako's energy.

570
01:13:09,920 --> 01:13:12,718
"There's no such thing"
as ghosts or the other world.'

571
01:13:13,560 --> 01:13:15,471
Takayama always criticised me.

572
01:13:17,000 --> 01:13:18,831
But Yoichi isn't strong enough to...

573
01:13:20,640 --> 01:13:21,789
What choice have we?

574
01:13:22,560 --> 01:13:24,312
What happens if the police come?

575
01:13:25,080 --> 01:13:28,914
He channels the energy.
A perfect medium.

576
01:13:32,440 --> 01:13:34,271
I'll do it.

577
01:13:40,280 --> 01:13:42,714
Do you have the same power
as Takayama?

578
01:13:43,640 --> 01:13:44,868
Yes.

579
01:13:45,240 --> 01:13:47,993
It doesn't mean you'll do better
as a medium than the boy.

580
01:13:49,960 --> 01:13:52,076
What if I watch the video...

581
01:13:54,080 --> 01:13:55,479
OK.

582
01:13:55,680 --> 01:13:58,752
- Then all we need is water.
- Water?

583
01:14:00,040 --> 01:14:02,315
Sea water doesn't permeate as well.

584
01:14:02,520 --> 01:14:06,069
We need a lot of fresh water
to absorb Sadako's fury.

585
01:14:38,200 --> 01:14:39,553
With this system,

586
01:14:39,760 --> 01:14:43,753
you conduct the energy he generates
into water, where it dissolves.

587
01:14:44,640 --> 01:14:46,517
Then Sadako will disappear.

588
01:14:56,160 --> 01:14:58,628
- OK. Are we ready?
- Yes.

589
01:15:01,360 --> 01:15:03,316
Take your place.

590
01:15:03,520 --> 01:15:04,669
Come.

591
01:15:21,360 --> 01:15:23,510
Remember, I'm on your side.

592
01:15:23,720 --> 01:15:24,869
OK?

593
01:16:14,280 --> 01:16:15,474
Let's start.

594
01:16:18,080 --> 01:16:19,479
Close your eyes.

595
01:16:20,880 --> 01:16:22,950
Remember what you saw.

596
01:16:23,800 --> 01:16:25,438
What did you see?

597
01:16:45,800 --> 01:16:47,028
Yes.

598
01:16:47,240 --> 01:16:49,151
Both your father and mother died.

599
01:16:49,360 --> 01:16:51,874
You are all on your own.
What did you see?

600
01:17:00,480 --> 01:17:01,913
Shall I tell you?

601
01:17:02,120 --> 01:17:05,510
Your mother died because of her.

602
01:17:06,560 --> 01:17:09,313
She betrayed her.

603
01:17:12,720 --> 01:17:13,789
Yes,

604
01:17:14,000 --> 01:17:15,672
it was my fault.

605
01:17:48,960 --> 01:17:49,915
It looks good.

606
01:17:50,120 --> 01:17:51,348
Keep it up.

607
01:18:10,920 --> 01:18:13,195
Dr Kawajiri, this is...

608
01:18:21,920 --> 01:18:24,388
..it is connected
to the other world...

609
01:18:36,440 --> 01:18:38,351
Sadako...

610
01:18:51,520 --> 01:18:53,511
Sadako...

611
01:18:57,840 --> 01:18:59,239
Take me...

612
01:19:00,480 --> 01:19:03,040
..and kill me.

613
01:19:04,200 --> 01:19:05,872
Take me...

614
01:19:07,520 --> 01:19:10,318
..and put an end to all this.

615
01:19:57,120 --> 01:19:58,633
Are you OK?

616
01:20:19,280 --> 01:20:20,793
Don't let go.

617
01:20:33,480 --> 01:20:35,516
Let me fall, and you'll be safe.

618
01:20:44,160 --> 01:20:49,757
"Frolic in brine, goblins be thine"

619
01:21:03,000 --> 01:21:04,752
Hold on to the wall.

620
01:21:04,960 --> 01:21:06,837
I can't support you by myself.

621
01:21:20,920 --> 01:21:22,478
Hold on to the wall.

622
01:21:26,680 --> 01:21:27,874
Mai...

623
01:21:30,440 --> 01:21:32,317
It's enough, it's over.

624
01:21:43,040 --> 01:21:44,439
Yoichi!

625
01:21:53,120 --> 01:21:54,519
Yoichi?

626
01:21:55,960 --> 01:21:57,598
Yoichi!

627
01:22:33,440 --> 01:22:34,953
Take him.

628
01:22:39,320 --> 01:22:40,673
Sir...

629
01:22:47,880 --> 01:22:49,199
Yoichi...

630
01:22:50,280 --> 01:22:52,475
Give your fear to me.

631
01:22:54,640 --> 01:22:56,312
Give it to me.

632
01:23:00,480 --> 01:23:01,435
Give it to me!

633
01:23:42,360 --> 01:23:43,315
Get away!

634
01:23:43,520 --> 01:23:44,873
Take the rope.

635
01:23:48,080 --> 01:23:49,479
Don't look back.

636
01:25:08,360 --> 01:25:10,157
Help... help...

637
01:25:10,360 --> 01:25:11,873
Help... help...

638
01:25:12,080 --> 01:25:13,513
Help...

639
01:25:21,320 --> 01:25:24,118
Why are you the only one saved?

640
01:26:27,720 --> 01:26:29,438
You're not still scared, are you?

641
01:26:33,080 --> 01:26:36,038
No. You?

642
01:26:36,640 --> 01:26:38,232
Me?

643
01:26:49,000 --> 01:26:51,116
I'm still scared, a bit.

644
01:27:02,040 --> 01:27:03,678
So how's Okazaki?

645
01:27:05,000 --> 01:27:07,150
Needs to be in hospital for a while.

646
01:27:07,360 --> 01:27:09,078
Hospital?

647
01:27:13,680 --> 01:27:16,069
Where's the key for this?

648
01:27:16,280 --> 01:27:17,679
Key?

649
01:27:20,800 --> 01:27:22,392
Is it this one?

650
01:27:27,960 --> 01:27:30,997
Mr Okazaki,
I need to take photos for your file.

651
01:27:31,200 --> 01:27:32,599
Look this way.

652
01:27:39,000 --> 01:27:40,194
Mr Okazaki...

653
01:27:40,400 --> 01:27:41,992
face this way.

654
01:27:44,640 --> 01:27:45,789
Here you go.

655
01:27:47,880 --> 01:27:49,632
Thank you.

656
01:28:46,040 --> 01:28:48,429
CAST

657
01:28:49,040 --> 01:28:53,272
Miki Nakatani

658
01:28:54,040 --> 01:28:58,238
Hitomi Sato

659
01:28:58,920 --> 01:29:03,152
Kyoko Fukada

660
01:29:30,160 --> 01:29:33,630
Nanako Matsushima

661
01:29:35,280 --> 01:29:38,556
Hiroyuki Sanada

662
01:31:08,840 --> 01:31:13,436
Directed by
Hideo Nakata

